channel.title: Animals Alphabetically
channel.description: Every Tuesday, biologist John Doe and wildlife photographer Foo Bar introduce you to a new animal.

item.title: Aardvark
item.description: With an English name adapted directly from Afrikaans -- literally meaning "earth pig" -- this fascinating animal has both circular teeth and a knack for digging.

item.title: Alpaca
item.description: Thousands of years ago, alpacas were already domesticated and bred to produce the best fibers. Case in point: we have found clothing made from alpaca fiber that is 2000 years old. How is this possible, and what makes it different from llamas?
